## One architectural enhancement I'd strongly recommend

Introduce a **fourth role**: the **Devil's Advocate AI**.

Unlike operational AI employees, its sole purpose is to challenge assumptions, search for blind spots, identify unintended consequences, and argue the strongest opposing case before major decisions are finalized.

This role should **never** have authority to execute actions—it only critiques and stress-tests plans. In real executive teams, this function often prevents groupthink. For NeuroCore, it would significantly improve the quality of strategic decisions and make the platform's reasoning more robust and explainable.

If Simulation-5 can demonstrate high-quality decision-making, evidence-based debate, adaptive learning, and transparent reasoning under uncertainty, you'll be evaluating something much closer to an autonomous enterprise than a sophisticated workflow engine.
